gomodel:SYNGO_4827  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6, 8: postembedding immunogold labeling of climbing fiber synapses localized protein 4.1N (EPB41L1) to the PSD from E19 until P7, while at later timepoints it was associated with intracellular organelles, the cytoskeleton, and the plasma membrane. Protein 4.1N could also be detected presynaptically.\n\nFigure 7: Protein 4.1N (and SAP97/DLG1) colocalized with GluR1 (GluA1/GRIA1) in Purkinje cells at early ages.\n\nProtein 4.1N (EPB41L1), a neuronal homolog of protein 4.1R, associates with actin cytoskeleton (PMID:10414974, PMID:11604393).. Experimental description: M&M: \"postnatal Sprague-Dawley rats were used in these experiments\"\n\nantibody:\nRabbit polyclonal anti-4.1N (serum; m4.1N), peptide sequence: N-terminus of mouse 4.1N, source: PMID:10414974\n\nto double-check the identity of the protein with street-name 4.1N; nucleotide BLAST of \"CCTCTGTGAAGAGATCCTGG\" primer used in northern blot in PMID:10414974 returns NM_001258331 as first hit (gene=EPB41L1)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4827" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

